      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KINTIRE RUSH (8) scored a decisive win when resuming last week at this venue, cruising home by 20 metres in an emphatic display. That continued her consistent form from the maiden campaign and was her first hitout for eight months so she should be better for it. Draws on the back row this time but has upside. PARIS PRINCESS (4) was only 2.3 metres away in second at this circuit and distance at her first outing back from a spell last week. Draws a few spots wider but should be fitter so can keep the ball rolling. NIGHT TO REMEMBER (3) has ground to make up on KINTIRE RUSH through the last-start second but she does draw better than that rival. MY ROCK MOVES (1) will be cherry-ripe after four runs back from a spell and was beaten only 1.4m when starting from this barrier last week.",
